<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="1738" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="7.[144,1104,1365,1556]" box="[144,276,1365,1389]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1738">
<heading box="[144,276,1365,1389]" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="7" pageNumber="1738" reason="5">
<emphasis box="[144,276,1365,1389]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1738">Distribution</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[144,1104,1365,1556]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1738">
Circumtropical; eastern and western Atlantic (
<bibRefCitation author="Marcus EBR" box="[663,810,1405,1429]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1738" pagination="841 - 874" refId="ref11969" refString="Marcus EBR. 1955. On the Anaspidae (Gastropoda, Opisthobranchia) of the warm waters of the Western Atlantic. B Mar Sci. 22: 841 - 874." type="journal article" year="1955">Marcus 1955</bibRefCitation>
) as well as the Indian and Pacific Oceans (
<bibRefCitation author="Kay EA" box="[324,435,1437,1461]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1738" pagination="173 - 189" refId="ref11417" refString="Kay EA. 1964. The Aplysiidae of the Hawaiian Islands. Proc Malacological Soc London. 36: 173 - 189." type="journal article" year="1964">Kay 1964</bibRefCitation>
), in shallow marine habitats. In 
<collectingCountry box="[806,865,1437,1461]" name="Chile" pageId="7" pageNumber="1738">Chile</collectingCountry>
this species has been recorded in Iquique (
<geoCoordinate box="[379,472,1469,1493]" degrees="20" direction="south" minutes="11" orientation="latitude" pageId="7" pageNumber="1738" precision="925" value="-20.183332">
20°11 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[443,449,1469,1493]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1738">ʹ</emphasis>
S
</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[484,590,1469,1493]" degrees="70" direction="west" minutes="08" orientation="longitude" pageId="7" pageNumber="1738" precision="925" value="-70.13333">
70°08 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[548,554,1469,1493]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1738">ʹ</emphasis>
W
</geoCoordinate>
), 
<collectingRegion box="[610,748,1469,1493]" country="Chile" name="Antofagasta" pageId="7" pageNumber="1738">Antofagasta</collectingRegion>
(
<geoCoordinate box="[763,856,1469,1493]" degrees="23" direction="south" minutes="38" orientation="latitude" pageId="7" pageNumber="1738" precision="925" value="-23.633333">
23°38 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[827,833,1469,1493]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1738">ʹ</emphasis>
S
</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[869,972,1469,1493]" degrees="70" direction="west" minutes="24" orientation="longitude" pageId="7" pageNumber="1738" precision="925" value="-70.4">
70°24 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[933,939,1469,1493]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1738">ʹ</emphasis>
W
</geoCoordinate>
) and Taltal (
<geoCoordinate box="[151,246,1501,1525]" degrees="25" direction="south" minutes="24" orientation="latitude" pageId="7" pageNumber="1738" precision="925" value="-25.4">
25°24 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[216,222,1501,1525]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1738">ʹ</emphasis>
S
</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[259,364,1501,1525]" degrees="70" direction="west" minutes="29" orientation="longitude" pageId="7" pageNumber="1738" precision="925" value="-70.48333">
70°29 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[323,329,1501,1525]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1738">ʹ</emphasis>
W
</geoCoordinate>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Castilla JC &amp; Uribe M &amp; Bahamonde N &amp; Clarke M &amp; Desqueyroux-Faundez R &amp; Kong I &amp; Moyano H &amp; Rozbaczylo N &amp; Santelices B &amp; Valdovinos C &amp; Zavala P" box="[387,599,1501,1525]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1738" pagination="213 - 232" refId="ref9326" refString="Castilla JC, Uribe M, Bahamonde N, Clarke M, Desqueyroux-Faundez R, Kong I, Moyano H, Rozbaczylo N, Santelices B, Valdovinos C, Zavala P. 2005. Down under the southeastern Pacific: marine non-indigenous species in Chile. Biol Invasions. 7: 213 - 232." type="journal article" year="2005">Castilla et al. 2005</bibRefCitation>
). This species was found for the first time in 
<collectingRegion box="[144,282,1532,1556]" country="Chile" name="Antofagasta" pageId="7" pageNumber="1738">Antofagasta</collectingRegion>
in 1982 (
<bibRefCitation author="Tomicic J" box="[390,545,1532,1556]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1738" pagination="209 - 213" refId="ref14062" refString="Tomicic J. 1985. Efectos del Fenomeno El Nino 1982 - 83 en las comunidades litorales de la Peninsula de Mejillones. Invest Pesq (Chile). 32: 209 - 213." type="journal article" year="1985">Tomicic 1985</bibRefCitation>
), associated with ENSO events.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[144,891,1627,1691]" box="[144,613,1627,1651]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1738">
<heading box="[144,613,1627,1651]" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="7" pageNumber="1738" reason="5">
<emphasis box="[144,613,1627,1651]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1738">Possible mechanism of introduction/Status</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[144,891,1627,1691]" box="[144,891,1667,1691]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1738">
Associated with ENSO events/unestablished (
<bibRefCitation author="Castilla JC &amp; Uribe M &amp; Bahamonde N &amp; Clarke M &amp; Desqueyroux-Faundez R &amp; Kong I &amp; Moyano H &amp; Rozbaczylo N &amp; Santelices B &amp; Valdovinos C &amp; Zavala P" box="[660,875,1667,1691]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1738" pagination="213 - 232" refId="ref9326" refString="Castilla JC, Uribe M, Bahamonde N, Clarke M, Desqueyroux-Faundez R, Kong I, Moyano H, Rozbaczylo N, Santelices B, Valdovinos C, Zavala P. 2005. Down under the southeastern Pacific: marine non-indigenous species in Chile. Biol Invasions. 7: 213 - 232." type="journal article" year="2005">Castilla et al. 2005</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="1739" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[212,1172,168,264]" box="[212,310,168,192]" pageId="8" pageNumber="1739">
<heading box="[212,310,168,192]" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="8" pageNumber="1739" reason="5">
<emphasis box="[212,310,168,192]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="1739">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[212,1172,168,264]" pageId="8" pageNumber="1739">
This is a large herbivorous marine slug, feeding almost exclusively on the alga 
<taxonomicName authority="(Frings and Frings 1965)" baseAuthorityName="Frings and Frings" baseAuthorityYear="1965" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Ulva" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="1739" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lactuca">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="1739">Ulva lactuca</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Frings H &amp; Frings C" box="[307,575,240,264]" pageId="8" pageNumber="1739" pagination="211 - 217" refId="ref10518" refString="Frings H, Frings C. 1965. Chemosensory bases of food-finding and feeding in Aplysia juliana (Mollusca, Opisthobranchia). Biol Bull. 128: 211 - 217." type="journal article" year="1965">Frings and Frings 1965</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. UA, SA.
</paragraph>
